134. Inachiae rates. Inachus, the tutelary god of the stream which bore the same name, and his son Phoroneus,

were the personages to whom the inhabitants of Argolis con- sidered themselves indebted for a knowledge of the useful arts and the establishment of social order. Hence Inachius became equivalent to Argivus and so to Graecus. The pat- ronymic Inachides is applied by Ovid both to Epaphus whom Io daughter of Inachus bore to Jupiter, and also to a more remote descendant, the hero Perseus, son of Jupiter

and Danae.
